cular English form of   Cecilia ."],"variants":[{"name":"Cecilie","meanings":["Medieval vernacular English form of   Cecilia ."]},{"name":"Cicely","meanings":["Variant of   Cecily .  This was a common form of the name in the Middle Ages, and in the 20th century was well known as the name of the British actress and singer  Cicely Courtneidge  (  1893–1980 )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":22,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":47,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Cecily Pecche was born in 1268, in Paston, Norfolk, England, her father, Simon Peche, was 19 and her mother, Julia Glanville, was 22. She married Walter de Paston in 1288, in Paston, Norfolk, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1323, in her hometown, at the age of 55, and was buried in Paston, Norfolk, England."},"et":{"1268–1323":"1268–1323","1255–1290":"1255–1290","1290–1348":"1290–1348","1249–1335":"1249–1335","1246–Female":"1246–Surnud","1315":"1315","1249":"1249","1348":"1348","1335":"1335","1268":"1268","1323":"1323","1246":"1246","1288":"1288","1255":"1255","1290":"1290","1317":"1317","Paston, Norfolk, England":"Paston, Norfolk, England"},"fi":{"1268–1323":"1268–1323","1255–1290":"1255–1290","1290–1348":"1290–1348","1249–1335":"1249–1335","1246–Female":"1246–Kuollut","1315":"1315","1249":"1249","1348":"1348","1335":"1335","1268":"1268","1323":"1323","1246":"1246","1288":"1288","1255":"1255","1290":"1290","1317":"1317","Paston, Norfolk, E